The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 1: The government has cleared 21 FDI proposals worth Rs 84.90 crore, including investments by Germanys BASF and Ventureast Trustee Company. Among the 14 proposals deferred was Vijay Mallya-run United Breweries plan to raise Rs 708 crore through convertible warrants to FirStart Inc.                            
	 Mumbai, July 1: Sebi has slapped a penalty of Rs 15 lakh on Triumph International Finance, a Ketan Parekh entity, for violating takeover regulations in relation to Adani Exports (AEL). Triumph had not disclosed to Sebi that various Ketan Parekh entities had bought shares of AEL crossing its threshold limit of 5 per cent.                             
	 Mumbai, July 1: Reliance Mutual Fund has received a good response to its Reliance Infrastructure Fund scheme, which closed for subscription last month and mobilised Rs 2,350 crore from investors.                            
	 New Delhi, July 1: Insurance regulator IRDA has prohibited insurance firms from investing in Indian depository receipts, the instruments through which foreign companies raise funds from the Indian market.                            
	 New Delhi, July 1: Income tax assessees whose tax is deducted or collected at source will have to quote a Unique Transaction Number from next year.                                                                                                                            
